short_answers.label: Introduction
short_answers.value:
I think if I had to boil myself down to one passion I would say it’s probably connecting with people in meaningful ways. I’ve been on a kind of internal journey this past year where I’m realizing more strengths I didn’t know I had and working on a way to exhibit those within my life.

  I’m a tax accountant by trade, something I somewhat excel at, but I have felt a sort of void within those roles that I recognized this past year.  I am working towards fulfilling myself in more meaningful ways outside of just my work or my career.

As for me I’m relatively easy going as long as I’m not hangry - nutri-grain and chewy bars come highly recommended and snickers bars for emergencies only. I think I’m very very funny, people tell me I am I promise, but I would say it’s a 70/30 split of laughing at me vs laughing with me.  I enjoy and prefer quality time and intimate setting with people but can also hang out at a venue/bar even though I may get tired at like 10:30 ????.  I’m very open minded and really pride myself on trying to see where people are coming from. I believe in compromise and sacrifice if someone else really holds something valuable in their life, and I believe in making room for multiple opinions to exist within a relationship - most decisions can be made through dialogue and understanding what is really cornerstone to each individuals life and values.  That’s kind of a basic personality outline, all my quirky weird humor and personality can be better outlined in person.

I enjoy sports, I collect whiskey, and I hunt about once a year. I enjoy time outside despite it never being my first option. Recently began working out regularly so Orange Theory membership would be a huge plus to do workouts together.

short_answers.label: Ideal Match
short_answers.value: Someone who isn’t soft spoken and knows themself. Can challenge me on things constructively and is open to the same from me. Someone who I could spend every day with and look forward to the next. Enjoys weird humor and can handle both being roasted and enjoys roasting people back. Bachelor/Bachelorette nights highly encouraged. Michelle’s season is coming up. Don’t judge me because I already judge myself.  But basically someone pretty open minded and able to communicate their emotions and thoughts without having to be pressed about it.

short_answers.label: Faith
short_answers.value: To be totally honest this is my first time on a faith based ap like this. I was born a Catholic but really never understood the purpose, significance and commitment something like that entails until recently. Someone in my life brought me back into the Church and I almost immediately experienced personal growth that I genuinely believe was God working in my life. I am working towards better understanding my faith and the role it plays in my life. I’ve had a barrier/compartmentalization of my physical and spiritual lives for most of my life, and now I am working towards better understanding, developing, and uniting those aspects of myself to really build myself up from.  I am confirmed in the Church and fully aware of the proceeding and significance of the Mass, but I am working towards discovering the social impact and teachings of the church to both better my faith and establish the type of Catholic I was to be for myself, my friends and my family.
